event_name: LOVE ME JEJE: AN AFRO-RNB EXPERIENCE NANAIMO
description: Back by Popular Demand! LOVE ME JEJE: AN AFRO-RNB EXPERIENCE Returns To Victoria — Immerse in this unique experience on February 27 @Evolve. LOVE ME JEJE: AN AFRO-RNB EXPERIENCE 2026 KICKOFF TOUR - NANAIMO. Come join us for a night of soulful vibes and groovy tunes at EVOLVE NIGHTCLUB! Get ready to dance the night away to the best of Afro-RnB music with a mix of old school classics and modern hits. Let the beats move you and the melodies serenade you as we celebrate love, life, and good music. Don't miss out on this unforgettable experience curated by our all star line up: DJ SEPS, DJ ASTRO, KONDUKTOR KREMA & OSITA DAVID.

event_name: A Night Under the Stars - HSUSU GALA 2026
description: HSUSU’s Annual Gala, a formal evening celebrating the Faculty of Health Sciences community with dinner and an after-dinner dance party. Features include a formal sit-down buffet dinner, presentations, sponsor prize giveaways. Dress code: semi-formal. Bar service available (19+ with ID). Open to all, no SFU or Health Sciences student status required. Early bird tickets available until March 1.

event_name: PERMISSION - A 5Rhythms movement workshop with Anne Marie Hogya
description: PERMISSION is a weekend 5Rhythms® movement workshop exploring strength, vulnerability, authenticity and connection. All levels welcome. Tuition: CA$325 early, CA$355 standard, CA$385 full. Refunds up to 7 days before event.

event_name: Dynamic Piano Duo: Giulia Varga & Siro Saracino Concert
description: Dynamic Piano Duo in Vancouver: Varga & Saracino, one piano–four hands with Tchaikovsky, Grieg, Dvořák, Brahms, Piazzolla & more. Featuring works by Edvard Grieg, Antonin Dvorak, Sergei Rachmaninov, Piotr Tchaikovsky, Johannes Brahms, Dmitri Shostakovich, Sir Anthony Hopkins, Siro Saracino, and Astor Piazzolla.

event_name: Living Opera: A free event for kids, families, and educators
description: Dive into the world of new opera creation with teaching artists Geoff and Nadia! Step into the power of musical storytelling with teaching artists Geoff and Nadia! In this lively, hands-on workshop, students will explore how music communicates emotion and brings stories to life! Using active listening and collaboration, students will identify the emotions they hear in opera excerpts, and the types of musical language used to convey them. Featuring live opera singing, students will play an interactive game that explores how composers express feelings through sound, and how that adds depth to the story! No musical experience required, just bring your imagination!

event_name: Native Jazz Quartet at the FireHouse Arts and Events Center
description: THE NATIVE JAZZ QUARTET is a hard-swinging and high energy group based on the swing/bebop tradition using indigenous and folk melodies. Co-founded by Ed Littlefield (Lingít) and Christian Fabian in 2011; features Reuel Lubag (piano), Michael Glynn (bass) and Delbert Anderson (Diné) on trumpet. Performances blend cultural stories with high-energy jazz.

MONSTER ENERGY PRESENTS - SKIITOUR ! Hailing from the snow-covered peaks of Whistler, Canada, SkiiTour are known for their upbeat “feel-good house music that keeps the vibe groovy” (DJ Mag) while channelling a retro ski aesthetic. Their annual après-ski parties at Shambhala Music Festival, featuring snow cones & snow machines, are the stuff of legends, where the energy is so high it feels like the mountains themselves are dancing. They're a hot ticket on the live music scene, with a global touring schedule that packs in over 80+ shows each year including festival appearances at Friendship, Burning Man, Bass Coast, Snowbombing Canada and many more!
location: UPSTAIRS ENTERTAINMENT PRESENTS : THE FREE LABEL, Upstairs Entertainment Ltd, 15 Bastion Square, Vic, Unknown, BC, Canada

event_name: United Sound #4 Ft: Prezzy Pillo Andrea Wolf
dance_style: UKG, Speed Garage, Bassline, Jungle, Drum & Bass, Dubstep, Grime
description: A night built for bass lovers, two-steppers, ravers, and anyone who craves the irresistible energy of the UK scene. A celebration of UKG, Speed Garage, Bassline, Jungle, Drum & Bass, Dubstep, Grime — and every hybrid and evolution that carries that unmistakable British flavour. Featuring Prezzy, Pillo, Andrea Wolf. More than a club night — United Sound is a growing community. It’s a gathering place where diverse musical styles meet, where both newcomers and long-time ravers are welcome, and where connections are made through rhythm, culture, and the shared love of low-end frequencies.

SIXX PAXX – where emotions dance and dreams come alive!

location: 1528 Stelly's Cross, SAANICHTON, BC V8M 1S8, CA

description: This concert will include works by Mozart, Chopin, and Gershwin. Sara Davis Buechner returns with an exciting program of Handel, Mozart, Chopin, and colourful Spanish pieces by Federico Longás. The afternoon will end with virtuosic fireworks!
Beginner-friendly heels-inspired dance class led by Desirae “Dez” Barkman. Optional dinner & drinks at Fireside Grill after class. Tickets non-refundable but transferable. Ages 18+. Doors at 5:45 PM.
location: 4814 West Saanich, VICTORIA, BC V8Z 3H5, CA

description: Van Django is an acoustic string ensemble performing gypsy jazz. The concert features a clever mix of standards, classical ditties, rock homages and solid originals. The Upstairs Lounge is an all ages licensed restaurant and bar, with doors opening at 6 pm for dinner service. The concert starts at 7:30 pm and is described as a listening room event.
location: Oak Bay Recreation - Personal Training/Active Rehab, 1975 Bee, Victoria, BC, CA

event_name: Throwdown Thursday featuring Jacob Leger w/ Sail Cassady & Elise LeBlanc
description: Throwdown Thursday is The Duke Saloon's local music showcase, featuring indie-folk musician Jacob Leger, flamboyant LGBTQ2A-friendly indie-rocker Sail Cassady, and Victoria-based singer-songwriter Elise LeBlanc, rooted in classic country, Appalachia, and western swing. 19+ event.
location: The Duke Saloon, 502 Discovery St, Victoria, BC V8T 1G8, CA

event_name: Casino Country Night with The Rob Curtis Band
description: Enjoy a night of country music and dancing with The Rob Curtis Band. Doors 6:00 PM; free line dancing lesson 6:15–7:00 PM; Stephanie Greaves 7:00–8:00 PM; The Rob Curtis Band (with special guest Farrah Simpson) headlining 8:30–10:30 PM. Full bar service, spacious dance floor. Ages 19+. Refunds up to 3 days before event.

Join singer-songwriters John Rewers and Carla Olive for an all-inclusive Song Writers' Circle: inspiration, reflection, sharing, and creation. Bring instruments. Class size limit 14. Doors at 08:45 AM. Ticket sales end Thursday, March 19 at 2pm PST. No refunds.

The Sutcliffes perform an energetic Beatles-focused set covering early Beatles material and their influences to fill the dance floor. Doors open at 6:00 pm for dinner service; band starts at 7:30 pm. Organized by Beacon Ridge Productions. Tickets no longer available through Oak Bay Recreation Centre (contact Marie at 250-812-7978 to purchase). Refund Policy: No refunds.
location: Oak Bay Recreation - Personal Training/Active Rehab, 1975 Bee, Victoria, BC, CA

description: Soundtracks to bad decisions and lawn ornaments on your walk of shame. Supported by Ryan Patrick Haint and Noah and Maylee. 3 hours, in person. Refund Policy: No refunds.
location: 2716 Rock Bay, VICTORIA, BC V8T 4R9, CA

event_name: Bottle Painting Night at Salsa & Guacamole
description: Guided bottle painting session — all supplies provided. Food and drinks available for purchase. Tickets required — limited spots available. No refunds.

event_name: GREASE Presented by Triple Threat Performing Arts Society
description: Get ready to experience the magic of live theater at the Dave Dunnet Community Theatre from April 23rd to 26th, 2026. Join us for an unforgettable evening filled with music, dance, and laughter. Don't miss out on this iconic show that will transport you back to the 1950s with its catchy tunes and heartwarming story. Content Advisory: Course Language, Explicit/Suggestive Content, Mentions/Displays of Alcohol. Minors 14 years and younger must be accompanied by an adult.
location: 2009 Cadboro Bay, Victoria, BC V8R 5G4, CA
source: West Coast Triple Threat Performing Arts Society

event_name: The Concert Series at The Flamingo Room
description: A high-energy night of live music featuring Cyrus Jordan and Runner, presented by Vancouver Cocktail Week and The Flamingo Room. Enjoy Flor de Caña rum cocktails amidst a packed-house concert atmosphere. Includes a welcome cocktail and entry to both live performances. VIP booth option available. Ages 19+.
location: The Flamingo Room, 1214 Commercial, Vancouver, BC V5L 2T4, CA

event_name: BASS COAST PRE-PARTY w. Magugu, Ponda & Skerd
dance_style: dancehall, hip hop, dub, grime, bass, drum and bass
description: Dubversified & CMCT are thrilled to announce the 2026 Bass Coast Pre Party. Featuring the Pidgin Rap guru Magugu, with Ponda & Skerd on the decks all night long. Everyone who grabs an advance ticket will be entered to win one of two Bass Coast Festival passes. Magugu's global sound has been filling up dance floors with his pidgin rap style. Ages 19+. Refunds up to 7 days before event.

description: Live performance by Mustafa Sandal with DJ performance and dance show. Expect iconic hits, upscale venue experience. Dress code: stylish & elegant. Ages 19+. Duration ~6 hours 30 minutes. No refunds. Line-up subject to change. Contact for VIP/Sponsorship: 778-320-7203 / 604-8080803.
